title: Planned Parenthood Demonstrators Divided
text:
Supporters for and again Planned Parenthood rallied VENTURA, Calif. - 
Planned Parenthood supporters and opponents held side-by-side demonstrations on Sunday afternoon in Ventura.They held signs and cheered when passing cars honked in front of Planned Parenthood on Ralston St.Supporters said they are upset an arsonist targeted the Thousand Oaks location.They said don't want Congress to pull funding in the wake of a controversial video released by anti-abortion activists.Opponents said they believe Planned Parenthood is profiting from abortions and they want taxpayer money to be sent to clinics that don't perform abortions.Funding for Planned Parenthood has become a presidential campaign issue.The Planned Parenthood clinic damaged by arson fire will reopen on Monday morning.Ventura County Sheriff's deputies said they have surveillance video that shows a suspect, but they said releasing it to the public now might compromise their investigation.
